The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Samsung starts work on units

 OUR CORRESPONDENT

 New Delhi, Feb. 9: Samsung India Electronics today started work on its manufacturing facilities at Sriperumbudur near Chennai. The company plans to invest $100 million in phases by 2011 and will employ nearly 2,500 people.

 In this plant, Samsung will make colour televisions and colour monitors, refrigerators, washing machines, air conditioners and printers, said H.B. Lee, regional president and CEO for Samsung South West Asia HQ.

 The colour television and monitor facilities are expected to start production in August 2007 and will have capacities of 1.5 million and 1 million units per annum respectively. The company also plans to manufacture LCD TVs and LCD monitors here.

 Samsung India already has a facility at Noida (near Delhi) where it manufactures colour televisions and monitors, air conditioners and refrigerators.




